</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Weight Gain Plan (25-40 Normal)</h1>

        <h2>Diet Plan (Weekly Variation)</h2>
        <table border="1">
            <tr>
                <th>Day</th>
                <th>Breakfast</th>
                <th>Lunch</th>
                <th>Snacks</th>
                <th>Dinner</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Monday</td>
                <td>Scrambled eggs, whole grain toast, and orange juice</td>
                <td>Lean meat, quinoa, and steamed vegetables</td>
                <td>Yogurt with berries and granola</td>
                <td>Baked chicken, brown rice, and spinach salad</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Tuesday</td>
                <td>Oatmeal with nuts, banana, and honey</td>
                <td>Grilled salmon, mashed sweet potatoes, and steamed broccoli</td>
                <td>Peanut butter sandwich with whole wheat bread</td>
                <td>Turkey stir-fry with brown rice and mixed vegetables</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Wednesday</td>
                <td>Avocado toast with poached eggs and a smoothie</td>
                <td>Grilled chicken wrap with hummus and greens</td>
                <td>Handful of almonds and a protein shake</td>
                <td>Pasta with ground turkey and olive oil dressing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Thursday</td>
                <td>Chia seed pudding with walnuts and berries</td>
                <td>Beef stew with quinoa and mixed greens</td>
                <td>Cottage cheese with honey and nuts</td>
                <td>Grilled shrimp with brown rice and steamed carrots</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Friday</td>
                <td>Protein smoothie (banana, almond milk, protein powder)</td>
                <td>Grilled tofu with stir-fried vegetables and brown rice</td>
                <td>Greek yogurt with flaxseeds</td>
                <td>Salmon with roasted sweet potatoes and asparagus</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Saturday</td>
                <td>Omelet with cheese, whole wheat bread, and green tea</td>
                <td>Chicken curry with basmati rice and cucumber salad</td>
                <td>Cashews and a protein shake</td>
                <td>Grilled fish with baked potatoes and sautéed greens</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Sunday</td>
                <td>Boiled eggs with whole wheat toast and peanut butter</td>
                <td>Vegetable stir-fry with tofu and brown rice</td>
                <td>Protein bar and yogurt</td>
                <td>Grilled steak with mashed potatoes and green beans</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <h2>Gym Routine (Optimized for Strength & Endurance)</h2>
        <table border="1">
            <tr>
                <th>Day</th>
                <th>Workout</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Monday</td>
                <td>Strength Training (Upper Body: Bench press, pull-ups, shoulder press, bicep curls)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Tuesday</td>
                <td>Strength Training (Lower Body: Squats, lunges, deadlifts, calf raises)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Wednesday</td>
                <td>Cardio & Core (Jogging, rowing machine, planks, ab rollouts)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Thursday</td>
                <td>Strength Training (Full-Body: Deadlifts, rows, dips, leg press)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Friday</td>
                <td>Functional Fitness (Battle ropes, sled push, medicine ball throws)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Saturday</td>
                <td>Active Recovery (Yoga, swimming, or hiking)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Sunday</td>
                <td>Rest or Recovery</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
